discover the motives which influenced their actions. “The cottagers arose the next morning before the sun. The young woman arranged
the cottage and prepared the food, and the youth departed after the first meal. “This day was passed in the same routine as that which preceded it. The young
man was constantly employed out of doors, and the girl in various laborious
