  <data key="d3">had only one, which was father. The girl was called sister or Agatha, and the youth Felix, brother, or son . I cannot describe the delight I felt when I learned the ideas
appropriated to each of these sounds and was able to pronounce them. I
distinguished several other words without being able as yet to understand or
